  "text": "The Kafka ProduceRequest travels from the client producer through the following call chain to the broker's log append:\n\n1. **KafkaProducer.send()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java:829) - The public API entry point where applications call send(ProducerRecord). This method is overloaded with optional callback parameter and delegates to doSend().\n\n2. **RecordAccumulator.append()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:275) - Called from KafkaProducer's doSend() method, this queues the record into batches for efficient batching. It accumulates records into MemoryRecords instances to be sent to the server, handling memory management and partition selection.\n\n3. **Sender.sendProducerData()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:357) - A background thread method that checks ready batches from the accumulator, discovers partition leaders via metadata, and prepares ProduceRequests for transmission to broker nodes.\n\n4. **NetworkClient.send()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:541) - Called by Sender to send ClientRequest objects containing ProduceRequests to the broker. This is the low-level network transmission point that queues requests to the NIO selector.\n\n5. **ReplicaManager.appendRecords()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala:674) - The broker-side handler that receives the ProduceRequest and coordinates appending records to the partition log. It validates required acknowledgments, delegates to appendRecordsToLeader() for local append operations, builds produce partition status, and manages delayed produce handling.\n\nThe data flow follows: User Application → KafkaProducer.send() → RecordAccumulator.append() → Sender.sendProducerData() → NetworkClient.send() → Broker Receives ProduceRequest → ReplicaManager.appendRecords() → Log Append."
}

